deck: An Elseworlds film directed by Bruce Timm, where Superman is the son of Zod, Batman is a vampiric Kirk Langstrom, and Wonder Woman is Bekka, granddaughter of Highfather. Together, they are a formidable alliance against evil, but many fear their unchecked power.
description:
From animation legend Bruce Timm comes an all-new original movie. In an alternative history Zod is Superman's father, Batman is a vampiric Man-Bat, and Wonder Woman is the child of Ares, God of War. When these dark heroes form an alliance, the question everyone asks is will they save the world, or rule it?

A seemingly familiar skyline reveals itself, though upon closer inspection this is not the Metropolis we know.

Journey to an alternate universe where the Justice League is now a trio of unchecked power. Employing methods of intimidation and fear, this Superman, Batman and Wonder Woman deal justice with brute force. And when a group of famed scientists experiences a series of deadly "accidents," a government task force follows the trail of clues to the Tower of Justice.

It's a high-stakes game of intrigue, mystery and action that asks the question: How do you serve justice to those above the law?
name: Justice League: Gods & Monsters

deck: George Miller returns to the desolate world he created with "Fury Road", in which Mad Max Rockatansky joins forces with the Imperator Furiosa to free a group of slaves from the clutches of the insane warlord Immortan Joe.
description:
From director George Miller, originator of the post-apocalyptic genre and mastermind behind the legendary âMad Maxâ franchise, comes âMad Max: Fury Road,â a return to the world of the Road Warrior, Max Rockatansky.

Haunted by his turbulent past, Mad Max believes the best way to survive is to wander alone. Nevertheless, he becomes swept up with a group fleeing across the Wasteland in a War Rig driven by an elite Imperator, Furiosa. They are escaping a Citadel tyrannized by the Immortan Joe, from whom something irreplaceable has been taken. Enraged, the Warlord marshals all his gangs and pursues the rebels ruthlessly in the high-octane Road War that follows.

Tom Hardy (âThe Dark Knight Risesâ) stars in the title role in âMad Max: Fury Roadââthe fourth in the franchiseâs history. Oscar winner Charlize Theron (âMonster,â âPrometheusâ) stars as the Imperator, Furiosa. The film also stars Nicholas Hoult (âX-Men: Days of Future Pastâ) as Nux; Hugh Keays-Byrne (âMad Max,â âSleeping Beautyâ) as Immortan Joe; Nathan Jones (âConan the Barbarianâ) as Rictus Erectus; Josh Helman (âX-Men: Days of Future Pastâ) as Slit; collectively known as The Wives, Rosie Huntington-Whiteley (âTransformers: Dark of the Moonâ) is Splendid, Riley Keough (âMagic Mikeâ) is Capable, ZoÃ« Kravitz (âDivergentâ) plays Toast, Abbey Lee is The Dag, and Courtney Eaton is Fragile. Also featured in the movie are John Howard, Richard Carter, singer/songwriter/performer iOTA, Angus Sampson, Jennifer Hagan, Megan Gale, Melissa Jaffer, Melita Jurisic, Gillian Jones and Joy Smithers.

Oscar-winning filmmaker George Miller (âHappy Feetâ) is directing the film from a screenplay he wrote with Brendan McCarthy and Nico Lathouris. Miller is also producing the film, along with longtime producing partner, Oscar nominee Doug Mitchell (âBabeâ, âHappy Feetâ), and P.J. Voeten. Iain Smith, Graham Burke and Bruce Berman serve as executive producers.

The behind-the-scenes creative team includes Oscar-winning director of photography John Seale (âThe English Patientâ), production designer Colin Gibson (âBabeâ), editor Margaret Sixel (âHappy Feetâ), Oscar-winning costume designer Jenny Beavan (âA Room with a Viewâ), action unit director and stunt coordinator Guy Norris (âAustraliaâ), and makeup designer Lesley Vanderwalt (âKnowingâ).

deck: Prequel to 21st century re-imagined version of the 'Battlestar Galactica' television series.
description:
Battlestar Galactica: Blood & Chrome was a 10-part web series that was assembled as a pilot for a TV series telling the story of young pilot Bill Adama's first tour of duty during the First Cylon War.

"Episode 1"Released November 9, 2012
William Adama joins the military to fight in the First Cylon War. He's posted aboard the Battlestar Galactica after he tests amazingly well in simulator training. Once aboard, however, he's assigned to Wild Weasel, a Raptor troop carrier rather than a Viper fighter. His partner is veteran pilot Coker, whose final tour is almost up and is none too happy to be paired with the gung-ho newbie he calls "Husker". Commander Silas Nash, sends them on a cargo supply run and orders them to avoid enemy contact of any kind.
"Episode 2"Released November 9, 2012
Just prior to take-off, Coker and Husker learn the Wild Weasel's "cargo" is a civilian. In-flight they learn that she's a software engineer named Dr. Becca Kelly, and she is part of the team responsible for upgrading the Cylons to their present form when she worked for Graystone Industries. Once out of communications range of the Galactica, Dr. Kelly gives them new orders. Their actual mission is to renezvous with Colonial cruiser Archeron at the edge of Cylon controlled space. When they arrive they find a destroyed Archeron and are ambushed by a pair of Cylon Raiders.
"Episode 3"Released November 16, 2012

when the Raptor's weapons jam, Adama saves the day by "threading the needle" through the burnt-out remains of the Archeron, destroying the pursuing Cylon Raiders. As they are about to plot a course home, Dr. Kelly orders them to transmit a signal, much to Coker's chagrin. An immediate response comes. It's a set of coordinates. They head to the indicated location. When Husker awakens Dr. Kelly from a nap she calls him "Ezra". When he tells her this she tells him that she was married to Ezra Barzel, a war hero. When they reach the coordinates they find a graveyard of Colonial ships, and among them some survivors.

"Episode 4"Released November 16, 2012
Aboard a Battlestar, Dr. Kelly is send on a mission to Djerba, an unguarded ice planet deep in Cylon controlled space. The commander, Ozar, wants to use her own pilots but acquiesces to Dr. Kelly's request for Coker and Husker to take her in Wild Weasel. Too late they learn it's a suicide mission. One of the Viper pilots to escort Wild Weasel is going to be Lt. Jim Kirby, who Coker thought was dead after his ship was badly damaged in battle. Kirby tells Coker that their deaths were faked so that they could attack the Cylons from within. Coker tells Kirby that he's seen his wife and he has a son. The commander tells the crew that the fate of the war depends on Dr. Kelly's mission. They jump within range of the planet, but there is a Cylon Basestar nearby.
"Episode 5"Released November 23, 2012

The Basestar and the Battlestar, Osiris, engage in long range combat while Wild Weasel and it's escorts slip off to Djerba. Unfortunately the Osiris is badly damaged so Ozar rams the Basestar and detonates their nuclear ordnance on impact blowing the Basestar and themselves up. Meanwhile the mission is being run-down by three Cylon raiders. Kirby bugs-out, but the rest are able to destroy the pursuers and crash land on Djerba.

"Episode 6"Released November 23, 2012
After the crash, Husker and Coker argue over how to proceed. Dr. Kelly fires off a round to get their attention and then says the only thing they can do is proceed with the mission. They follow the distress signal to an ice cave where they find the Marine unit has been massacred but not by arms fire. There is a sudden floor collapses and Coker and Kelly fall into a pit. Husker attempts to rescue them but just ends up dropping down and getting stuck with them. Noises and movement can be heard. Suddenly they are attacked by an alien life form. Coker is bitten and things look grim until the only surviving Marine, Sgt. Toth rappels to their aid and kills the snake-like being.
name: Battlestar Galactica: Blood & Chrome

deck: Mad Max tells the story of vengeance and survival in a post-apocalyptic world that suffers from a societal breakdown. It follows the life of the MFP (Main Force Patrol) member known as Max Rockatansky as he tries to survive and protect those close to him.
description:
In a stunningly terrifying, post-apocalyptic world created by director George Miller nobody is safe. The film stars Mel Gibson as Max Rockatansky; a member of the MFP (Main Force Patrol) who has become sick and tired of his job. The desolate and never-ending stretches of highway that litter the Australian outback have been transformed into battlegrounds; stained with blood and covered in scraps of the drivers and vehicles that came before.

The world became a more violent and terrifying place with the introduction of savage biker gangs; roaming the wastes searching for those whom they can torture, rape and murder, their sick and twisted way of life. Max; who desires retirement, is brought back into the game after one of these gangs end up fatally injuring his best friend, Goose, while also killing Max's wife and child.

Far past his breaking point, Max ventures back into the wastelands in a souped-up V8 designed for speed and carnage.
name: Mad Max

It's up to the Dark Knight to stop this gruesome gang before they unleash 'digital laughter,' a computer virus that's part of a diabolical plan to jeopardize all of Gotham City's vital technology. Batman, Green Arrow, Cyborg, Nightwing and Red Robin must combine forces to battle these baddies and save the city.

description:
Suicide Squad follows the events of Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice, and takes place in a post-Superman world where the government tries to determine how to respond in the event that an alien with more villainous intentions visits Earth. Ruthless intelligence officer Amanda Waller (Viola Davis) offers to recruit societyâs worst criminals, those possessing lethal skills and superhuman powers. Her first target: the possessed archaeologist June Moone/Enchantress (Cara Delevingne).

When Midway City is threatened by a powerful mystical enemy, Wallerâs plan gets the go-ahead. She cuts deals with the whole squad of prisoners: Deadshot (Will Smith) gets his Second Amendment rights Â­reinstated, Harley (Margot Robbie) is set free from her cage, Diablo (Jay Â­Hernandez) steps out of his fireproof prison, Boomerang (Jai Courtney) and Slipknot (Adam Beach) each get to wield their signature weapons once more, and Killer Croc Â­(Adewale Akinnuoye-Â­Agbaje) emerges from the swamp. The only condition is this: Obey orders or die. This is strictly enforced by squad leader Rick Flag (Joel Kinnaman), the samurai Katana (Karen Fukuhara), and of course the explosive devices â developed by Wayne Enterprises â inserted into their necks. However, the arrival of the tatted-up Gotham City mega-criminal, the Joker (Jared Leto), might doom the mission thanks to his plan to reunite with his true love, Harley.
name: Suicide Squad

They cause a distraction by pretending to argue, and take out most of the gang, except for Spider-Man, who flees. Cap follows, and the chaos only ends when all the Spider-Men are dead. description: Super Hero High is buzzing with excitement over new student, Supergirl. But when Supergirl crash lands into the cafeteria, it's evident that though she has incredible power, she has a long way to go before she becomes a Super Hero. Too intimidated by the other supers to ask them for assistance, Supergirl turns to helpful I.T. girl, Barbara Gordon. Barbara takes Supergirl under her wing and introduces her to the sweet, old librarian, Granny Goodness. As Barbara helps Supergirl learn to harness her powers, Wonder Woman joins them and becomes a mentor and friend to Supergirl. Meanwhile, the Junior Detective Club (The Flash, Bumblebee and Hawkgirl) investigates a mysterious rash of security breaches centered around the teleportation "Boom Tubes."
